The normal version of SF2 is great, I got this one for the extra gems and infinite energy without ads. I wish that was the only change in the game, the way it is now there is no eclipse mode or enchanting, which takes away an entire layer of gameplay and makes it not as fun. Also, upgrade prices no longer scale in cost and there are only two upgrades per piece of equipment, this doesent seem like a problem initially but it just makes the game move way to fast. I only had to play survival once to beat lynx, and only because I wanted blood reaper rather than daggers. Additionally, there is no underworld, which is a great way to play when you want to use an outdated weapon, or just don't feel like progressing in the story. Overall, the game is great but would be much better if it were closer to the original.

Very fun base combat, but brought down by overpowered bosses, and overly 
damaging magic. The main games cycle is a pretty generic one, although it 
is still fun and engaging: fight to get money which allows you to get 
better equipment which allows you to fight harder fights. The magic is 
annoying but tolerable in most fights, it is easy to block it and take a 
fraction of the damage, but if you try to Dodge and fail, you will likely 
get half your health gone in an instant, like I said, frustrating when it 
happens, but tolerable. This is not the case in boss fights. Bosses 
normally have at least one passive ability, such as occasionally 
transferring half the damage you deal to it to you, one special move, such 
as stomping the ground and causing you to fall(usually doing a ridiculous 
amount of damage too), and a few magic spells. For the first two rounds 
they are a reasonable difficulty, like fighting a regular fight on hard, 
but on round three things change. It feels like they get a buff to damage 
and armour, and they spam their special move at every chance they get. If 
you fail to block or dodge, it can take over half of your health. This 
makes many bosses extremely frustrating to fight. At the time of writing 
this i am on the wasp fight, and her special move is extremely grating 
after having her on less than twenty percent health and having my health 
over eighty percent, to have her just kill me in two hits. I will likely 
update this review when I progress further.

You get to play with so many different weapons and you need to use different techniques to win. If I had to nitpick, I would call out 2 things. The first is that we are forced to change weapons as you power up since buying the new weapon is cheaper than trying to upgrade current weapon. But some weapons handle better than others but you can't continue with your favourite weapon. And second is, I have played the normal edition so I miss the imbue option. Still, no ads and unlimited energy is worth it! But miss some of the gameplay from the normal edition.

I am about to give you guys the real scoop about this app. The Good: Gems are farmable; you can have any weapon and armor set you ever wanted but were too broke to afford in the original by paying the $5.00 for this game, which to me was worth it. No ads and Infinite Energy are also BIG pluses. Sensei gets a little backstory as well. What It's Missing: No Eclipse Mode, No Awakening, No Enchanting Your Weapons, No Online Modes. Hopefully these things get added later, but it's not a detriment. The Bad: It Crashes. Like, a lot. Be prepared to get to Round 8 or 9 in Survival only to have the game crash and lose your progress. Until they fix that I will not rate it higher.
